 Seniors More Life Health - YouTube.";i:1;s:46:"Try these warm-up chair exercises for seniors.";i:2;s:94:"Sit up straight and slowly tilt your head toward your right shoulder until you feel a stretch.";i:3;s:80:"Hold this position while gradually extending your left arm down and to the side.";i:4;s:56:"You should feel a stretch on the left side of your neck.";i:5;s:44:"10 Back Strengthening Exercises for Seniors.";i:6;s:35:"These are beginner level exercises.";i:7;s:72:"The bent knee raise is an excellent beginner level exercise for seniors.";i:8;s:62:"It is simple and effective and it requires very little effort.";i:9;s:95:"This particular exercise is especially useful for increasing abdominal and lower back strength.";i:10;s:209:"To keep it secure think of using a strong clip or pin or try having a family member of the seniors help install a couple of shelving brackets to the back of the chair to keep the band positioned appropriately.";i:11;s:67:"Sit comfortably in the chair with the hips as far back as possible.";i:12;s:58:"Ensure that the back is firm to the backrest of the chair.";i:13;s:64:"For older adults Boehm recommends three exercises in particular.";i:14;s:23:"Anyone can do a bridge.";i:15;s:110:"You start in a recumbent position on your back and then lift and hold your buttocks off the ground Boehm says.";i:16;s:131:"Its effective because you create rigidity from the rib cage to the pelvis and all the way from the belly button around to the back.";i:17;s:76:"This exercise strengthens your abdominal muscles to protect your lower back.";i:18;s:76:"Sit up tall in your chair and lift your arms up in line with your shoulders.";i:19;s:33:"Make light fists with your hands.";i:20;s:71:"Inhale to twist your torso to the right and make a jab with your elbow.";i:21;s:90:"Exhale to twist back to center and use your abs to kick your left leg straight out and up.";i:22;s:201:"Exercise 4 Chair Marching First check your posture Lift alternate legs so that your feet lift about 2 inches from the floor and swing your arms forwards and back at a speed that is comfortable for you.";i:23;s:43:"Imagine you marching along at a brisk pace.";i:24;s:85:"Continue for about 20 30 seconds Benefits Improves circulation and warms the muscles.";i:25;s:67:"Sit in a chair with your back straight and your arms at your sides.";i:26;s:99:"Extend and straighten your right knee while focusing on squeezing your quadricep muscles which are.";i:27;s:59:"Sitting CHEST STRETCH A B This stretch is good for posture.";i:28;s:48:"Sit upright and away from the back of the chair.";i:29;s:34:"Pull your shoulders back and down.";i:30;s:28:"Extend arms out to the side.";i:31;s:82:"Gently push your chest forwards and up until you feel a stretch across your chest.";i:32;s:102:"Sit up straight in your chair with your feet flat on the floor and your back away from the chair back.";i:33;s:70:"If its comfortable reach back and place your palms on your lower back.";i:34;s:57:"Otherwise put them on your hips or rest them on your lap.";i:35;s:121:"Sit up tall in a comfortable supportive chair and then raise both shoulders up back then down creating a circular motion.";i:36;s:52:"Try to repeat this exercise 10 times before resting.";i:37;s:96:"The chair should have a back to prevent you from falling backward in case you lose your balance.";i:38;s:45:"Slowly bend your knees and begin to sit down.";i:39;s:65:"Lean your chest forward but remember to keep your torso straight.";i:40;s:78:"When your backside touches the chair immediately begin to stand back up again.";i:41;s:93:"This chair exercise for seniors helps improve mobility and strength throughout the lower leg.";i:42;s:108:"Sit and keep your back straight on the chair and place your feet on the floor with about hip-distance apart.";i:43;s:41:"Look straight ahead and engage your core.";i:44;s:81:"Starting with the right foot and lift the heel off the ground as high as you can.";i:45;s:27:"This helps engage the calf.";i:46;s:77:"Stretch your right arm outward and back towards the right side of your chair.";i:47;s:36:"Then stretch down towards the floor.";i:48;s:35:"Keep this position for two seconds.";i:49;s:43:"Then go back to a straight seated position.";i:50;s:38:"Perform this process for the left arm.";i:51;s:53:"Repeat this five times alternating between both arms.";i:52;s:59:"Seated Crunches - Activates the muscles around the abdomen.";i:53;s:101:"This is a great treatment for back pain exercise for tired or sore backs after a long day of walking.";i:54;s:66:"This back strengthening exercise will firm your abdominal muscles.";i:55;s:63:"It will help your ability to get out of bed or up from a chair.";i:56;s:19:"Arm Raises On Back.";i:57;s:74:"This back muscle exercise improves the range of motion in your upper back.";i:58;s:99:"If you are an exercise leader review pages 5 and 6 to see a brief description of all the exercises.";i:59;s:50:"When you are ready to start these chair exercises.";i:60;s:138:"For the first time go to Module A pages 7 to 13 and do the warm-up and exercises on several different occasions until you are comfortable.";i:61;s:182:"Chair exercises for seniors have many great health benefits that reduce the effect of any pre-existing health condition and improve your overall functional quality of life including.";i:62;s:87:"Keep your blood pressure under controlled reducing the risk of coronary heart diseases.";i:63;s:29:"Helps build lean muscle mass.";i:64;s:87:"Improves your bones health thereby safeguarding you from fibromyalgia and osteoporosis.";i:65;s:55:"Improves your insulin resistance and glucose tolerance.";i:66;s:26:"Add strength to your back.";i:67;s:50:"Free Back Strengthening Exercise Plan for Seniors.";i:68;s:77:"Below is an exercise plan with 7 exercises that do not require any equipment.";i:69;s:69:"This can be done at home and targets the upper middle and lower back.";i:70;s:58:"Some exercises may be performed on the bed floor or chair.";i:71;s:67:"Hyperlinks are attached to each listed exercise for demonstrations.";i:72;s:49:"How to do Bridging More Back and Trunk Exercises.";i:73;s:143:"Make sure to sign up for my Eldergym Senior Fitness Newsletter to make the most of these exercises and receive my free 4 week exercise program.";i:74;s:29:"Eccentric Straight Leg Raise.";i:75;s:157:"This exercise works your abdominal and hip flexor muscles which will improve your ability to get out of bed get out of a chair and maintain your posture and.";}}